1
00:00:04,928 --> 00:00:10,469
This is the foundation of spiritual life, 
spiritual aspiration—

2
00:00:10,469 --> 00:00:13,723
is recognising
our own deficiencies;

3
00:00:13,723 --> 00:00:18,495
a candid assessment 
of our situation.

4
00:00:18,495 --> 00:00:20,830
So, recognising 
our own imperfections,

5
00:00:20,830 --> 00:00:24,659
[From Imperfection to Perfection]

6
00:00:24,659 --> 00:00:28,991
but realising that 
this element within us

7
00:00:28,991 --> 00:00:31,732
in the midst 
of so much imperfection,
 

8
00:00:31,732 --> 00:00:38,655
that seeks perfection, is something
very valuable, that tendency.

9
00:00:38,655 --> 00:00:42,728
So even in the midst
of so much imperfection

10
00:00:42,728 --> 00:00:47,096
there’s this tendency 
to search for perfection,

11
00:00:47,096 --> 00:00:50,186
the ideal, 
the Absolute.

12
00:00:50,186 --> 00:00:56,430
And he [Guru Mahārāj] says,
that tendency, it’s weak.

13
00:00:56,430 --> 00:00:58,926
We’re told,
jīva is an impoverished śakti,

14
00:00:58,926 --> 00:01:03,563
she needs to gain some wealth,
some capital

15
00:01:03,563 --> 00:01:07,843
from a superior servitor,
āśrayāḥ-vigraha, chit-śakti—

16
00:01:07,843 --> 00:01:11,831
come under their guidance 
and influence.

17
00:01:11,831 --> 00:01:14,698
He said, so this tendency
to seek perfection

18
00:01:14,698 --> 00:01:18,105
is very weak, otherwise
we would have it by now,

19
00:01:18,105 --> 00:01:21,214
we would have attained it.

20
00:01:21,214 --> 00:01:26,625
But, he said, so that’s 
the nature of the finite

21
00:01:26,625 --> 00:01:29,239
is to be subjected 
to imperfection.

22
00:01:29,239 --> 00:01:37,264
But that points to the need—
we have to address that,

23
00:01:37,264 --> 00:01:41,916
to fulfil that, it’s beyond ourselves,
is outside of ourselves.

24
00:01:41,916 --> 00:01:46,957
He said, so that makes room
for the guru, or the guide,

25
00:01:46,957 --> 00:01:49,799
which is the functioning
principle of Divinity

26
00:01:49,799 --> 00:01:53,171
revealing Himself 
in this world.

27
00:01:53,171 --> 00:01:54,281
And here, 
Guru Mahārāj says,

28
00:01:54,281 --> 00:02:02,655
“And the Perfect, by dint
of being the perfect,

29
00:02:03,808 --> 00:02:07,068
the means 
for revealing Himself

30
00:02:07,068 --> 00:02:10,425
is something native to Himself.

31
00:02:11,405 --> 00:02:15,660
It’s the Infinite who can make Itself
known to the finite,”

32
00:02:15,660 --> 00:02:18,065
as Guru Mahārāj said,
“Otherwise He is not Infinite”.

33
00:02:18,065 --> 00:02:20,774
And therein lies 
our prospect,

34
00:02:20,774 --> 00:02:25,971
and that’s the beauty,
mysterious charm

35
00:02:25,971 --> 00:02:29,041
of Kṛṣṇa consciousness—

36
00:02:29,041 --> 00:02:32,640
[It] is coming in connection 
with the Infinite,

37
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:36,296
the Supreme Lord,
the Supreme Absolute Truth,

38
00:02:36,296 --> 00:02:38,726
Reality the Beautiful,

39
00:02:38,726 --> 00:02:42,576
by connecting with His agent,

40
00:02:42,576 --> 00:02:47,349
divine agency, Śrī Guru, 
the divine guide.

41
00:02:48,909 --> 00:02:51,239
Because, and Guru Mahārāj
deals with this also, and he said,

42
00:02:51,239 --> 00:02:57,417
“One might think, ‘Well,
you can get all this internally,

43
00:02:57,417 --> 00:02:59,953
what is the need of help
outside yourself?’”

44
00:02:59,953 --> 00:03:07,032
He said, but that voice within us
is often unreliable;

45
00:03:07,792 --> 00:03:11,322
we cannot discern
the voice of God,

46
00:03:11,322 --> 00:03:13,038
the voice of Divinity,

47
00:03:13,038 --> 00:03:15,985
from our own 
speculative imaginings

48
00:03:15,985 --> 00:03:22,650
or wishful thinking,
or selective remembrance.

49
00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:26,542
So, he said, very mercifully
Kṛṣṇa comes before us

50
00:03:26,542 --> 00:03:30,540
as the guide, or the guru, 
to guide us

51
00:03:30,540 --> 00:03:35,269
from the world of imperfection
towards the world of perfection,

52
00:03:35,269 --> 00:03:42,857
by activating 
our serving capacity.

